00:09:19.112 --> 00:09:22.892
helped define the first degron in this work from

161
00:09:23.012 --> 00:09:26.972
2016. And what you can do with these is you can find structural features in

162
00:09:27.012 --> 00:09:30.052
neo-substrate proteins, and you can map them.

163
00:09:30.192 --> 00:09:34.152
And for the cereblon system, we have this G loop that enables you to prospectively

164
00:09:34.192 --> 00:09:34.692
annotate

165
00:09:35.892 --> 00:09:39.332
potential neo-substrates. We looked for this feature, and we couldn't find this

166
00:09:39.392 --> 00:09:42.852
feature either. So that wasn't found in any of the experimental structures, and it

167
00:09:42.892 --> 00:09:46.012
wasn't found in any of the predicted structures that were available either.

168
00:09:47.052 --> 00:09:49.112
But we did have one positive indication.

169
00:09:49.752 --> 00:09:53.642
And so Neomorph was founded with a collaboration with the Center for

170
00:09:53.732 --> 00:09:56.392
Protein Degradation at the Dana-Farber Cancer Institute.

