673
00:39:51.996 --> 00:39:55.416
will you be missing out something that derived from the CD4 engagement?

674
00:39:55.476 --> 00:39:59.196
Because on your earlier data, you showed that CD4 does contribute to

675
00:39:59.256 --> 00:40:00.856
antitumor activities. Thank you.

676
00:40:02.056 --> 00:40:05.536
Both very good questions. If I start with the second one, yes,

677
00:40:06.136 --> 00:40:10.076
we've looked into that a lot about whether directing to CD8s

678
00:40:10.136 --> 00:40:11.816
could have any kind of detrimental effect.

679
00:40:12.436 --> 00:40:16.196
But I'd really like to emphasize here that the strategy is to

680
00:40:16.276 --> 00:40:16.916
bias it.

681
00:40:18.176 --> 00:40:20.716
It's not selective. There's not a complete

682
00:40:21.836 --> 00:40:25.476
lack of effect on CD4s, and we definitely also see a bit of

683
00:40:25.496 --> 00:40:29.276
indirect activation of the CD4s. So the CD4s are likely

684
00:40:29.296 --> 00:40:32.196
still able to deliver at the right amount,

685
00:40:33.076 --> 00:40:36.956
the activity that they give. Because when we look in our

686
00:40:36.976 --> 00:40:40.495
preclinical assays, we don't see any detrimental effect, even in

687
00:40:40.536 --> 00:40:43.716
durability, in all sorts of aspects of this

688
00:40:44.116 --> 00:40:46.516
reduced engagement of the CD4s.

689
00:40:48.596 --> 00:40:50.316
And I've forgotten the first half of the question, sorry.

690
00:40:50.926 --> 00:40:50.926
ADA.

691
00:40:50.956 --> 00:40:51.496
Oh, ADA.

692
00:40:52.396 --> 00:40:56.116
So ADA generation, unfortunately, preclinical models are not very good at

693
00:40:56.136 --> 00:40:59.276
predicting accurately how ADA

694
00:41:01.256 --> 00:41:05.196
will be in patients. So I think we'll have to find that one out in

695
00:41:05.216 --> 00:41:08.966
the clinic. But we've not had any red flags in anything we've been doing that

696
00:41:08.996 --> 00:41:12.896
suggests that biasing to the CD8s is increasing our ADA risk.

697
00:41:14.336 --> 00:41:15.996
I'm more thinking about reducing though.

698
00:41:16.756 --> 00:41:17.376
Oh, reducing? No.

699
00:41:17.976 --> 00:41:18.276
Thank you.

700
00:41:19.716 --> 00:41:20.016
Over here.

